#: ../../source/reference/tensor/generated/maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.rst:2
msgid "maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:1 of
msgid "Draw samples from a log-normal distribution."
msgstr "从对数正态分布中抽取样本。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:3 of
msgid ""
"Draw samples from a log-normal distribution with specified mean, standard"
" deviation, and array shape.  Note that the mean and standard deviation "
"are not the values for the distribution itself, but of the underlying "
"normal distribution it is derived from."
msgstr ""
"从具有指定均值、标准差和数组形状的对数正态分布中抽取样本。请注意，这里的"
"均值和标准差不是分布本身的值，而是其来源的正态分布的值。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal of
msgid "参数"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:8 of
msgid "Mean value of the underlying normal distribution. Default is 0."
msgstr "底层正态分布的均值。默认为0。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:10 of
msgid ""
"Standard deviation of the underlying normal distribution. Should be "
"greater than zero. Default is 1."
msgstr "底层正态分布的标准差。应大于零。默认为1。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:13 of
msgid ""
"Output shape.  If the given shape is, e.g., ``(m, n, k)``, then ``m * n *"
" k`` samples are drawn.  If size is ``None`` (default), a single value is"
" returned if ``mean`` and ``sigma`` are both scalars. Otherwise, "
"``np.broadcast(mean, sigma).size`` samples are drawn."
msgstr ""
"输出形状。如果给定的形状是例如 ``(m, n, k)``，则抽取 ``m * n * k`` 个样本"
"。如果 size 是 ``None``（默认），且 ``mean`` 和 ``sigma`` 都是标量，则"
"返回单个值。否则，抽取 ``np.broadcast(mean, sigma).size`` 个样本。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:18 of
msgid "Desired chunk size on each dimension"
msgstr "每个维度上期望的块大小"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:20 of
msgid "Allocate the tensor on GPU if True, False as default"
msgstr "如果为 True，则将张量分配在 GPU 上，默认为 False"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:22 of
msgid "Data-type of the returned tensor."
msgstr "返回张量的数据类型。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal of
msgid "返回"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:25 of
msgid "**out** -- Drawn samples from the parameterized log-normal distribution."
msgstr "**out** -- 从参数化的对数正态分布中抽取的样本。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal of
msgid "返回类型"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:30 of
msgid ":py:obj:`scipy.stats.lognorm`"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:31 of
msgid ""
"probability density function, distribution, cumulative density function, "
"etc."
msgstr "概率密度函数、分布、累积密度函数等。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:34 of
msgid "备注"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:35 of
msgid ""
"A variable `x` has a log-normal distribution if `log(x)` is normally "
"distributed.  The probability density function for the log-normal "
"distribution is:"
msgstr ""
"如果变量 `x` 的对数 `log(x)` 服从正态分布，则 `x` 服从对数正态分布。对数"
"正态分布的概率密度函数为："

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:39 of
msgid ""
"p(x) = \\frac{1}{\\sigma x \\sqrt{2\\pi}}\n"
"e^{(-\\frac{(ln(x)-\\mu)^2}{2\\sigma^2})}\n"
"\n"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:42 of
msgid ""
"where :math:`\\mu` is the mean and :math:`\\sigma` is the standard "
"deviation of the normally distributed logarithm of the variable. A log-"
"normal distribution results if a random variable is the *product* of a "
"large number of independent, identically-distributed variables in the "
"same way that a normal distribution results if the variable is the *sum* "
"of a large number of independent, identically-distributed variables."
msgstr ""
"其中 :math:`\\mu` 是变量对数的正态分布均值，:math:`\\sigma` 是其标准差。"
"当一个随机变量是大量独立同分布变量的 *乘积* 时，其结果服从对数正态分布，"
"这与变量是大量独立同分布变量的 *和* 时服从正态分布类似。"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:51 of
msgid "引用"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:52 of
msgid ""
"Limpert, E., Stahel, W. A., and Abbt, M., \"Log-normal Distributions "
"across the Sciences: Keys and Clues,\" BioScience, Vol. 51, No. 5, May, "
"2001. http://stat.ethz.ch/~stahel/lognormal/bioscience.pdf"
msgstr ""
"Limpert, E., Stahel, W. A., 和 Abbt, M., \"对数正态分布在科学中的应用："
"关键与线索\", BioScience, 第51卷, 第5期, 2001年5月. http://stat.ethz.ch/~"
"stahel/lognormal/bioscience.pdf"

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:56 of
msgid ""
"Reiss, R.D. and Thomas, M., \"Statistical Analysis of Extreme Values,\" "
"Basel: Birkhauser Verlag, 2001, pp. 31-32."
msgstr ""
"Reiss, R.D. 和 Thomas, M., \"极值的统计分析\", 巴塞尔: Birkhauser 出版社,"
" 2001年, 第31-32页."

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:60 of
msgid "示例"
msgstr ""

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:61 of
msgid "Draw samples from the distribution:"
msgstr "从分布中抽取样本："

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:68 of
msgid ""
"Display the histogram of the samples, along with the probability density "
"function:"
msgstr "显示样本的直方图以及概率密度函数："

#: maxframe.tensor.random.lognormal.lognormal:82 of
msgid ""
"Demonstrate that taking the products of random samples from a uniform "
"distribution can be fit well by a log-normal probability density "
"function."
msgstr ""
"演示从均匀分布中随机抽取样本并取其乘积后，可以很好地拟合对数正态"
"概率密度函数。"

